<header>
	Look at the following statements about the speaking exam and decide whether they are true or false.
</header>
	
<section id="body">
  <img class="rightFloat" src="../media/ED_SP_002.jpg" mode="1" id="1001"/>
  <br/>
  <ol id="questionList">
    <br/>
    <li id="q1">You will have to talk about yourself.<a id="a1">True</a><tab/><a id="a2">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q2">The Examiner will ask you to call him or her Mr/Ms X.<a id="a3">True</a><tab/><a id="a4">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q3">You need to have a lot of information about a lot of topics.<a id="a5">True</a><tab/><a id="a6">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q4">The Examiner will ask all the questions.<a id="a7">True</a><tab/><a id="a8">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q5">The interview time will vary a little from candidate to candidate.<a id="a9">True</a><tab/><a id="a10">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q6">You can ask about your marks.<a id="a11">True</a><tab/><a id="a12">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q7">The Examiner may judge you partly on your appearance.<a id="a13">True</a><tab/><a id="a14">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q8">The Examiner will ask where you are from.<a id="a15">True</a><tab/><a id="a16">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q9">Giving examples to support your opinion will help you do better.<a id="a17">True</a><tab/><a id="a18">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q10">The discussion topic will be chosen by the Examiner.<a id="a19">True</a><tab/><a id="a20">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q11">You are required to have definite opinions.<a id="a21">True</a><tab/><a id="a22">False</a><br/></li>
    <br/>
    <li id="q12">You must communicate, no matter what topic is presented.<a id="a23">True</a><tab/><a id="a24">False</a><br/></li>
  </ol>
</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">1. You will probably be asked about what you do and where you are from.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">2. Examiners will give you their full name and will not ask you to call them anything.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">3. This test is about communication not knowledge. </font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">4. You can ask examiners to repeat a question but you shouldn't ask them anything else.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">5. The exam is between 11 and 14 minutes.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">6. You will find out how well you did when you get your exam results, no sooner!</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">7. Looking nice helps with the impression you give but the examiner is there to mark your communication.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb8">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">8. It is a good idea to give some extra information as the examiner may not know your country very well.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb9">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">9. Giving examples and explanations is always a good idea.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb10">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">10. Examiners have several topics to choose from.</font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb11">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">11. You are only expected to communicate your thoughts, not have definite opinions. </font>
  </p>
</section>

<section id="fb12">
  <p align="left">
    <font face="verdana" size="13" color="#000000">12. You should do your best with whichever topic you get.</font>
  </p>
</section>

